h atrial fibrillation or those who have undergone coronary artery bypass grafting (CABG). In addition, the application of medications aimed at controlling hypertension is crucial. Hypertension is a significant risk factor for coronary heart disease, and antihypertensive drugs such as calcium channel blockers and angiotensin receptor blockers (ARBs) are essential in managing elevated blood pressure. The market also sees the inclusion of medications used for symptom management, such as nitrates and other vasodilators, which help alleviate angina symptoms by improving blood flow to the heart. Together, these applications underscore the multifaceted approach required to address coronary heart disease effectively.</p></p><p id="" class=""><strong>Download Full PDF Sample Copy of Reseach Report @ <a target="">https://www.verifiedmarketreports.com/download-sample/?rid=687674&utm_source=GitHub&utm_medium=278</a></strong></p><h3 id="" class="">Who is the largest manufacturers of&nbsp;Coronary Heart Disease Medication Market worldwide?</h3><h3 class=""></Li><Li>AstraZeneca</Li><Li> Pfizer</Li><Li> Novartis</Li><Li> Merck & Co</Li><Li> Bayer</Li><Li> Buchang Pharmaceutical</Li><Li> China Resources Pharmaceutical</Li><Li> Tasly Pharmaceutical</Li><Li> Yiling Pharmaceutical</Li><Li> China Shineway Pharmaceutical</Li><Li> Shanghai Pharmaceuticals</Li><Li> Green Valley</h3><h3 id="" class="">Coronary Heart Disease Medication Market &nbsp;Segments Analysis</h3><p id="" class="">Using a deliberate segmentation strategy, the Coronary Heart Disease Medication Market research report provides an in-depth analysis of numerous market segments, including application, type, and location. This method gives readers a complete grasp of the factors that propel and impede each industry in order to achieve the high standards of industry stakeholders.</p><h3 id="" class="">Coronary Heart Disease Medication Market &nbsp;By Type</h3><p></Li><Li>Nitrates</Li><Li> Thrombolytic Drugs</Li><Li> Î² - rece